Package org.apache.zookeeper.server.backup

Class BackupFileInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.zookeeper.server.backup.BackupFileInfo
  • public class BackupFileInfo
extends java.lang.Object
    Metadata for a file that has been backed-up Assumes that the name of the backed up file uses the format: prefix.lowzxid-highzxid where prefix is one of the standard snap or log file prefixes, or "lostLog". In the case of timetable backup file, it takes a format of timetable.lowTimestamp-highTimestamp.

                      long modificationTime,
                      long size)
        Constructor that pulls backup metadata based on the backed-up filename
        Parameters:
        backedupFile - the backed-up file with the name in the form prefix.lowzxid-highzxid for example snapshot.9a0000a344-9a0000b012. if timetable backup, ranges are decimal longs (posix timestamps)
        modificationTime - the file modification time
        size - the size of the file in bytes
